          "text": "Summer into AI 2026"
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " hosted by "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "link",
              "attrs": {
                "href": "https://advisoryhour.substack.com",
                "target": "_blank",
                "rel": "noopener noreferrer nofollow",
                "class": null
              }
            }
          ],
          "text": "@advisoryhour"
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " — theme: Data.Punk."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "attrs": {
        "textAlign": null
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The FDA's Adverse Event Reporting System (FAERS) holds over 30 million reports from patients, doctors, and pharmacists about drug side effects — filed after drugs are already on shelves. Most people never see this data. Side Effect Oracle pulls it in real time, stacks the actual post-market reports against the official label language, and has Claude reason through the gaps with extended thinking. Type a drug name and watch the FDA's own data reveal what the label doesn't say."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "textAlign": null,
        "level": 2
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "How the AI works"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "bullet_list",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "list_item",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "attrs": {
                "textAlign": null
              },
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ],
                  "text": "Dual FDA data fetch"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " — The app simultaneously queries the FDA FAERS reaction-count endpoint (top 25 adverse reactions by report volume) and the FDA drug label database (adverse_reactions, warnings, warnings_and_cautions fields). Both run in parallel before Claude sees anything."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "list_item",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "attrs": {
                "textAlign": null
              },
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ],
                  "text": "Extended thinking + streaming dossier"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " — Claude claude-sonnet-4-6 with extended thinking (budget: 6,000 tokens) receives both datasets in a single message. It reasons through label-vs-reality gaps before writing the dossier, which streams live to the screen section by section: [DRUG PROFILE], [TOP REPORTED REACTIONS], [LABEL vs REALITY], [UNDERSTANDING THE NUMBERS], [QUESTIONS FOR YOUR DOCTOR]."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "list_item",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "attrs": {
                "textAlign": null
              },
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ],
                  "text": "Collapsible reasoning trace"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " — The thinking block streams separately and collapses into a toggle so you can see exactly what Claude weighed before concluding."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "textAlign": null,
        "level": 2
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "How to play"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "bullet_list",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "list_item",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "attrs": {
                "textAlign": null
              },
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Type any drug name — generic names work best (ibuprofen, metformin, sertraline, lisinopril)"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "list_item",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "attrs": {
                "textAlign": null
              },
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Click "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ],
                  "text": "QUERY FDA"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " — the app fetches both FAERS reaction data and the official label simultaneously."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "list_item",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "attrs": {
                "textAlign": null
              },
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Watch the side-by-side panels: animated reaction bars on the left, FDA label text on the right"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "list_item",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "attrs": {
                "textAlign": null
              },
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Read the streaming dossier as Claude reasons through what the numbers reveal — especially the [LABEL vs REALITY] section"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "list_item",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "attrs": {
                "textAlign": null
              },
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Expand the reasoning trace to see Claude's chain of thought before the dossier was written"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
